Looking at the code, I need to analyze the contract of `Map::rfold`:

**Contract:**
- **Preconditions:** None beyond type constraints; defined for any `Map`, `init`, and `g`.
- **Postcondition:** `Map { iter, f }.rfold(init, g) == iter.rfold(init, |acc, elt| g(acc, f(elt)))` ‚Äî equivalently, fold the elements in right-to-left order with `f` applied to each before `g`.
- **Edge case:** When `iter` is empty, neither `f` nor `g` is called; the result is `init`.

